		<div class="comment_header">
		Comment <a href="#c_1713661082">13</a> by Raymond Camden
		posted on 1/6/2007 at 2:28 AM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>I'll ditto some of Brian's comments. The UI you can do with Flex is far more powerful then what you can do with HTML, and 100% compatible as long as you have Flash (which is at what - 110% penetration? ;). You also get media abilities like streaming music. You can even talk to a web cam if you wanted.</p><p>Don't forget that Flash Remoting is _very_ slim. Perhaps not as slim as JSON.</p><p>Also look at Flex Data Services. That is pretty much impossible with AJAX (unless you want to do a lot of polling).</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
<div class="comment" id="c_1713661087">
	<div>
		<img src="//a.disquscdn.com/1611874952/images/noavatar32.png" class="comment_author_profile_pic">
