	<div>
		<div class="comment_header">
		Comment <a href="#c_1713661087">14</a> by Rachel Maxim
		posted on 1/6/2007 at 4:46 AM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>I'm in the process of wrapping up a Flex app for which I researched and presented both Flex and Ajax as options, and we of course, chose Flex in the end. Here are our reasons:<br>- No cross-browser issues to deal with<br>- Tight CF/Flex integration (RPC, CF-to-Flex objects etc)<br>- Low cost and quick ramp to productivity ($900 for FB2, immediate results - no mucking around with limited documentation or figuring out someone else's code)<br>- Commercially supported product<br>- Slick appearance (I'm a designer first and foremost, so this is always important to me :)</p><p>And lastly, it was my preference for ActionScript 3 over JavaScript as a lauguage to write that sealed the deal.</p><p>Hope that helps someone!</p></div>
	</div>
</div>
		
